cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.DC 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on vehicular ad hoc networks (VANETs) which are a type of wireless ad hoc network. 
2. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper proposes a trust management framework for secure routing in VANETs, indicating a focus on security. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a separation of the forwarding and control planes in VANETs, which is a control system design approach. 
4. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the use of on-demand distance vector routing (TAODV) protocol and presents a new routing protocol named software-defined trust based ad hoc on-demand distance vector routing (SD-TAODV), indicating a focus on information theory. 
5. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper proposes a software-defined approach to VANETs, which involves distributed computing and networking.
